H3599.desc: a <def>cup</def>; also a <def>bag</def> for money or weights; bag, cup, purse.

H3600.desc: a <def>cooking range</def> (consisting of two parallel stones, across which the boiler is set); ranges for pots.

H3612.desc: <def>Caleb</def>, the name of three Israelites; Caleb.

H3613.desc: <def>Caleb-Ephrathah</def>, a place in Egypt (if the text is correct); Caleb-ephrathah.

H3614.desc: a <def>Calebite</def> or descendant of Caleb; of the house of Caleb.

H3641.desc: <def>Calneh</def> or <def>Calno</def>, a place in the Assyrian empire; Calneh, Calno. Compare <w src="H3656">3656</w>.

H3677.desc: properly, <def>fulness</def> or the <def>full moon</def>, i.e. its <def>festival</def>; (time) appointed.

H3841.desc: <def>Libnah</def>, a place in the Desert and one in Palestine; Libnah.

H3870.desc: <def>Luz</def>, the name of two places in Palestine; Luz.

H8646.desc: <def>Terach</def>, the father of Abraham; also a place in the Desert; Tarah, Terah.

H8650.desc: a <def>pole</def> (as a mast or flagstaff); beacon, mast.

H8651.desc: a <def>door</def>; by implication, a <def>palace</def>; gate mouth.

H8654.desc: a <def>Tirathite</def> or inhabitant of an unknown Tirah; Tirathite.

H8655.desc: <def>Teraphim</def> (singular or plural) a family idol; idols(-atry), images, teraphim.

H8656.desc: <def>Tirtsah</def>, a place in Palestine; also an Israelitess; Tirzah.

H8659.desc: <def>Tarshish</def>, a place on the Mediterranean, hence, the ephithet of a merchant vessel (as if for or from that port); also the name of a Persian and of an Israelite; Tarshish, Tharshish.

H8660.desc: the title of a Persian deputy or <def>governor</def>; Tirshatha.

H8662.desc: <def>Tartak</def>, a deity of the Avvites; Tartak.

H8663.desc: a <def>crashing</def> or loud <def>clamor</def>; crying, noise, shouting, stir.

H8664.desc: a <def>Tishbite</def> or inhabitant of Tishbeh (in Gilead); Tishbite.

H8666.desc: a <def>recurrence</def> (of time or place); a <def>reply</def> (as returned); answer, be expired, return.

H8668.desc: <def>rescue</def> (literal or figurative, persons, national or spiritual); deliverance, help, safety, salvation, victory.
